he 28th, after which it will be best to write to Montreux whence my mail will be forwarded. We are planning to spend August at a place near Cannes.

With regard to your request for autographs for the Cheltenham Festival, I regret to say that I never give autographs and cannot make an exception that would automatically involve me in more and more autographing.





Very sincerely yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: GEORGE WEIDENFELD

CC, 1 p.





Montreux, September 25, 1962

Palace Hotel

Dear Ge